{{Expand German|Augustenburger Briefe|date=September 2010}}
The '''Augustenburger Briefen''' (''Augustenburg Letters'') are a collection of letters on aesthetics written by [[Friedrich Schiller]] in 1793 to [[Frederick Christian II, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg|Friedrich Christian von Augustenburg]]. They represent an early draft of what would be published in 1795 as ''Über die ästhetische Erziehung des Menschen in einer Reihe von Briefen'' ("Letters on the aesthetic education of man"), but were believed lost in a fire. They were only published, on the basis of surviving copies, in 1875.

