The '''''Russian Biographical Dictionary''''' (RBD, {{lang-ru|Русский биографический словарь}}) is a [[Russian-language]] [[biographical dictionary]] published by the [[Russian Historian Society]] edited by a collective with [[Alexander Polovtsov]] as the [[editor-in-chief]]. The dictionary was published in 25 volumes from 1896 to 1918 and considered as one of the most comprehensive Russian biographical sources for the 19th and early 20th century period.

